_meanings:
A woman who either
goes to meet her lover or keeps an
appointment made by him;  
<ls>Ku. 6. 43</ls>; <ls>R. 16. 12</ls>; {#aBisArayate kAMtaM#}
{#yA manmaTavaSaMvadA . svayaM vABisaratyezA#} 
{#DIrEruktA'BisArikA#} <ls>S. D. 115</ls>;  
{#kAMtArTinI tu yA yAti saMketaM sABisArikA#} <ls>Ak.</ls>
The directions as to dress &c. to be
observed by the different kinds of
{#aBisArikA#} are given in <ls>S. D. 116.</ls>
The <ls>S. D.</ls> further recommends the
following {8} places as eligible spots
for lovers to meet:-- (1) a field; (2)
a garden; (3) a ruined temple; (4)
the house of a female messenger; 

(5) forest; (6) caravansary (a place
for pilgrims &c.); (7) a cemetery,
and (8) the bank of a river; {#kzetraM#} 
